{
  "manifest": {
    "schemaVersion": 1,
    "name": "calculator",
    "title": "Calculator",
    "entrypoint": "index.html",
    "bindings": [],
    "capabilities": [],
    "preferredSize": {
      "w": 3,
      "h": 4
    }
  },
  "files": {
    "README.md": "# calculator\n\nA pure, fully self-contained widget: no bindings, no capabilities, no data\nrequests. Everything happens client-side with plain event listeners.\n\nUseful as the minimal-footprint starting point for a widget that doesn't\nneed any dashboard data at all — a small tool, converter, or reference view.\nIt still sends `dashboard:ready` on load for protocol consistency, but that\nis the only message it sends; the parent has no obligation to reply to\nanything since no `getData`/`getTheme`/`sendPrompt` request is ever made.\n\nSee `docs/authoring.md` for the full protocol this template intentionally\nuses the least of.\n\n---\n\nAdapted from the reference implementation's documentation (openclaw/openclaw#101136 series).\n",
    "index.html": "<!doctype html>\n<!--\n  calculator — a pure, fully self-contained widget: no bindings, no\n  capabilities, no data requests. Shows the protocol floor: it still sends\n  dashboard:ready on load for consistency, but that's the only message it\n  ever sends or expects a reply to.\n-->\n<html lang=\"en\">\n  <head>\n    <meta charset=\"utf-8\" />\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n    <title>Calculator</title>\n    <style>\n      :root {\n        color-scheme: light dark;\n      }\n      body {\n        margin: 0;\n        padding: 10px;\n        font-family: var(--font-mono, ui-monospace, monospace);\n        background: Canvas;\n        color: CanvasText;\n      }\n      #display {\n        text-align: right;\n        font-size: 1.4rem;\n        padding: 8px;\n        margin-bottom: 8px;\n        border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, CanvasText 25%, transparent);\n        border-radius: 6px;\n        overflow-wrap: anywhere;\n      }\n      #keys {\n        display: grid;\n        grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);\n        gap: 6px;\n      }\n      button {\n        font: inherit;\n        padding: 8px 0;\n        border-radius: 6px;\n        border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, CanvasText 25%, transparent);\n        background: transparent;\n        color: inherit;\n        cursor: pointer;\n      }\n    </style>\n  </head>\n  <body>\n    <div id=\"display\">0</div>\n    <div id=\"keys\"></div>\n    <script>\n      // Accumulator-style calculator: combines numbers with one pending\n      // operator at a time. No eval() — just enough logic to prove out a\n      // self-contained widget with zero dashboard data.\n      var display = document.getElementById(\"display\");\n      var acc = null,\n        op = null,\n        entry = \"0\",\n        fresh = true;\n      var OPS = {\n        \"+\": function (a, b) {\n          return a + b;\n        },\n        \"-\": function (a, b) {\n          return a - b;\n        },\n        \"*\": function (a, b) {\n          return a * b;\n        },\n        \"/\": function (a, b) {\n          return b === 0 ? NaN : a / b;\n        },\n      };\n\n      function render() {\n        display.textContent = entry;\n      }\n\n      function pressDigit(d) {\n        entry = fresh\n          ? d === \".\"\n            ? \"0.\"\n            : d\n          : d === \".\" && entry.indexOf(\".\") !== -1\n            ? entry\n            : entry === \"0\" && d !== \".\"\n              ? d\n              : entry + d;\n        fresh = false;\n        render();\n      }\n\n      function pressOp(key) {\n        var value = parseFloat(entry);\n        acc = acc === null ? value : fresh ? acc : OPS[op](acc, value);\n        op = key === \"=\" ? null : key;\n        entry = String(acc);\n        fresh = true;\n        if (key === \"=\") acc = null;\n        render();\n      }\n\n      function pressClear() {\n        acc = null;\n        op = null;\n        entry = \"0\";\n        fresh = true;\n        render();\n      }\n\n      [\"7\", \"8\", \"9\", \"/\", \"4\", \"5\", \"6\", \"*\", \"1\", \"2\", \"3\", \"-\", \"0\", \".\", \"=\", \"+\", \"C\"].forEach(\n        function (key) {\n          var button = document.createElement(\"button\");\n          button.type = \"button\";\n          button.textContent = key;\n          button.onclick = function () {\n            if (key === \"C\") pressClear();\n            else if (OPS[key] || key === \"=\") pressOp(key);\n            else pressDigit(key);\n          };\n          document.getElementById(\"keys\").appendChild(button);\n        },\n      );\n\n      window.parent.postMessage({ v: 1, type: \"dashboard:ready\" }, \"*\");\n    </script>\n  </body>\n</html>\n"
  }
}
